utterances.utterance: Yeah, but you know what.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH

utterances.speaker: PERINO

utterances.utterance: All right. Stormy Daniels and her lawyer, Michael Avenatti, strike out again in their attempt to damage President Trump. Greg's monologue is next. And don't forget, follow us on social media for more behind the scenes action of "The Five." We'll be right back.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Just how bad is Michael Avenatti? He's so bad he give lawyers a bad name. A California judge not only ruled to dismiss Stormy Daniel's defamation suit against President Trump, but also ordered her to pay Trump's legal fees. Now, when judges do that it's to send a message, your lawyer is a moron. Poor Stormy, as a rule, people pay her for sex, now Avenatti reversed the charges. Sleazy lawyers are often called ambulance chasers. Avenatti is worse. He chases spot lights, and when he catches them he looks ridiculous. But he's good at one thing costing his own side money. A few months ago his firm was order to pay $10 million bucks to an attorney who once worked there. And what about the Kavanaugh debacle? The gang rape accusation arrived like the carnival side show the media so badly wanted. Avenatti was the clown with the biggest clip-on nose hocking his little horn. Then his disgusting ploy imploded. And the TV anchors who indulge him fled sensing they were becoming his victims too. But why complain? He's been a gift for the Republicans and a disaster for the Democrats. Are we sure he wasn't on Trump's payroll all along? Now, Avenatti has taken to challenging people to fight on twitter like a town Palooka relieving past fight at the local bar. So how does this serial trickster get away with it? Does the state bar care about ethics violations? Isn't there a disciplinary committee or is he exempt because he's a liberal attack dog.  His punishment should be harsh. Make him represent himself. All right, though, we do have -- he's going to run, Dana. I mean.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: He's running.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yeah. He is running. So, maybe this could be great for him. He doesn't care.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: He might be great for a time.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Being selfish because he does provide a lot of fodder. I'm sure the Democrats wish he would just go away.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: . or become a Republican.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He could run with Liz. What a ticket.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yeah. They can come up with some other, sort of.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, exactly.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I do wonder if Avenatti will actually help Stormy Daniels pay the actual legal fees.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, the best part is her Go-Fund Me page which is, you know, flooded with money from people who hate Trump, that's going to end up going to Trump.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Right, exactly.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I don't know if that's true. I just read that.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And in Trump's twitter it's true, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Trump always makes money (INAUDIBLE) the guy is very rich. I think the Democrats have really hitched their ride to the wrong horse here.  I'm not talking about Stormy, I'm talking about Avenatti because he's taken the Democrats for a ride and it's not going to be a victory lap here. And so the president, obviously, said that she's a horse-face or whatever on twitter, and now anybody on the left is upset about that. I wouldn't say that, but here's what I would say, the left has used the word C word to describe people in the Trump family and then everybody applauded that.  They fantasized about killing the president. They've called him a fatso, Nazi, mental patient. They've loved that kind of language. And now, all of a sudden, they're clutching their pearls when the president says the word horse face? Please. To be surprised now that Donald Trump says bad thing and uses dirty nicknames about people three years later, either you haven't learned a thing after the last three years or you're just dense.  This is what he does and this is how he wins. And now, regarding the other claim about the gang rape case, that being so false in and of itself makes me think maybe Donald Trump didn't have an affair with Stormy Daniels.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Hmm. Well -- go ahead.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: I would say that Stormy Daniels have also said not so nice thing about President Trump's appearance. So, he's kind of just giving it back to her.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Very specific ones.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Very specific things we will not repeat. Avenatti 2020 is going to be lit, as the kids say. And I think Democrats are really, actually, pretty disappointed that he's gotten involved here, especially during the Kavanaugh fight. They think the reason they lost that is because he got involved with the ridiculous allegations and these statements that were made. And the bottomline is he's putting Stormy Daniels in a position where she's probably not going to pay these legal bills for her, and he's going to go and try to find some other woman to jump into this trap of politics saying -- they're claiming he will represent her, it will be great, they're going to win, and yet his track record shows exactly the opposite. So it's not good for women getting involved. Warning, you see Avenatti knocking on your door, say no and tell him to go away. And when it comes to actual implications and compliments for what he's done legally.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Tell me, the kids say his campaign is lit?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Lit.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I mean, he's like.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Like on fire.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: It's going somewhere.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It's going to be exciting to watch.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, I think Dana and Greg had it right. It will be fun for us because.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: That's what I mean.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: To me, the horse face stuff, by the way.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yeah.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: . I don't like -- come on. This is -- I mean, you're going to say to me, oh, it's typical Trump, that's what he does with everybody.  But, you know, remember Carly Fiorina? She's -- look at that face. This woman is horse face. And I just think, man, at some point American women will be like, this guy is out of control.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I don't know if American women side with porn stars, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, I see. I see. Well, I just think it's all woman is the terms of his attitude. But I think the real interesting thing here is how the right is making this out to be such a big win, total vindication for Donald Trump, when this is not even the main case. The main case has to do with the non-disclosure agreement. This was about that unknown guy in the parking lot.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Do you think that people really care about the non-disclosure agreement.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: . details of what they did, what they didn't do.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: My point to you is that this case is still pending.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: It's still out there. It's not settled.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right. But here's the issue, this was -- this case that they -- Trump just won was probably the strongest one because to your point about the hush agreement she took the money. It will be really hard in court for her to be proven to be right if she had taken the money.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But it's not. She said that, in fact, it wasn't properly signed, and that Michael Cohen who now -- I don't know where he stands -- I don't think he's.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Democrat again.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I don't know. But I'm saying that how -- this is where the conversation -- and not only at this table but in America has gone.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Thanks to who? Michael Avenatti.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS

utterances.utterance: Oh, I see.

utterances.utterance: Michael Avenatti actually went and had his DNA tested, 25 percent reptile.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Liberal hypocrisy on full display once again with the left proving it's OK to shame women as long as they're Republicans. Rapper T.I. is under fire over his new music video depicting the first lady as a stripper in an apparent dig at Kanye West meeting with President Trump.  The footage is so vulgar and profane we can't even show you most of it. In response, a spokesperson for Mrs. Trump says, quote, like or not, she's the first lady and this is the White House. It's disrespectful and disgusting to portray her this way simply because of politics. So little advise for T.I., when you're calling someone a racist, don't be sexist, right? Just try to stay out on your own way, T.I.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I also think it's unpatriotic. Melania Trump has done nothing to deserve that. And she's in Africa she said that she was probably the most bullied person in the world, which she is talking online. And I said -- when you're bullied online you feel like you're the most bullied person.  This takes it beyond just the online piece. This is going right into the pop culture. She had just traveled to Africa to help people there with -- she took books. She took the message that America is there to help you on health care, maternal health, she held all the babies. She did all the things that you would expect a first lady to do to show that you care about another country. And especially with Africa that have so much poverty, and she comes home to this. I mean, they should pull it but, unfortunately, everyone is making money out of this administration, right? From the right and the left, and -- but I really feel like first ladies should be off limits.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I did too. I wanted Michelle Obama speak up, Greg, she's former first lady. A powerful woman, I expect her to come to Melania's defense here.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right. I think you just laid down the gauntlet. I don't know.  The only thing -- when you showed that, now I want to go watch it.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I'm sure it's got ton of views right now.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: We probably would have done better if we'd just ignored it, but I'm really surprised a rapper has denigrated women, all this time when I hear their songs and hear B's and H's, I thought those were terms of endearment, so I don't think you should be surprise. But this was his response to Kanye. It wasn't a reputation of his ideas, you know, when he talked about stop and stop and frisk, or prison reform, or creation of ideas centers, or reigniting enterprise zones with tax relief, instead he went after Melania. I think it's just a grain of salt. Just ignore it.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: And Kanye and I run a twist, Juan, by saying that Donald Trump was dehumanizing someone using them as a prop. He did the exact same thing with a woman, Melania Trump.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS

utterances.speaker: WATTERS

I mean, gosh. You think about that kind of racist language. Or don't forget what happened -- I mean, even around here we've called her baby mama, she's Obama -- remember that kind of stuff?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, yeah.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Around here?

utterances.utterance: I won't get into it because I don't think it's necessary. But believe me, check the record and talk about Michelle Obama's weight as, oh, how can she be giving.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Do you think the idea was wrong?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You know what? I just think -- this is what I've said to you in the earlier segment, Jesse. I think this whole culture and the way that we talk about thing is going down the pipe.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, you're skirting the main issue and it's T.I. Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: I wonder when hip-hop is going to have their Me-Too movement because.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, my God.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: It is.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That would be.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Yeah. And instead of looking at his own record which includes serving 10 months in prison for violating his parole, possession of drugs, arrested multiple times as teenager for dealing drugs, felony weapons possession, instead of looking at his own life and going how can I improve the lives of people who are younger than I am, making sure that they don't go through this and learn from my mistakes, he's instead going after Melania Trump, the first lady, for a beef that he has with Kanye West by attacking her in this way. It's disgusting. He's not going to apologize for it. I don't expect him to. But the level of respect that has not been given to Melania as been given to other first ladies as in term of just the office really is astounding.

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Where's the feminists? I'm just wondering where's all the feminist.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Where's now.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Hey look. You know what? I'll tell you what. I don't understand why we have sunk to this level. And now you have a strict -- you know what?

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: This is one of them, Juan. This is a perfect example of that.  Respect the office of the first lady, whether it's Michelle Obama or Melania Trump.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But I'm telling you, Katie, this is where our politics is now.  It invites this kind of response and I don't think it's appropriate, but this is.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: By saying this invites the response, that's like saying Melania invited this.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You're saying it justifies what was done to the first lady.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No, I disagree, and I disapprove of T.I.'s action, but I can't - - I cannot honestly say that, oh, this is so different, so alarming than the kind of acrimony --

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: It is to the first lady.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- directed at Michelle Obama.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I would disagree with that. So Juan, will you be boycotting T.I. as the first lady --?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: It's not a problem. I don't listen to -- you know how I feel about the rap stars.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.utterance: I think this is something where people can relate to Elizabeth Warren being trolled this way by the president. You know, birtherism was anti-black. MARA GAY, "NEW YORK TIMES" EDITORIAL BOARD: In terms of the Elizabeth Warren -- the attack on Warren, I believe that was actually about white anxieties among Donald Trump's base about who's white in America.

utterances.utterance: Meanwhile, Rush Limbaugh offering his take on what's really going on here.

utterances.speaker: RUSH LIMBAUGH, RADIO TALK SHOW HOST

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: What do you think, kid?

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Well, I think that the reason we're here is because the left has so closely married identity politics to their ideas and to their strategy that Elizabeth Warren has marched herself into this. So they are so focused on skin color and gender that they can't divorce themselves from those issues when it comes to actually talking about their ideas, and that's where we are. But I want to take President Trump out of this. Yes, he has mocked Elizabeth Warren. Yes, he has called her Pocahontas. The allegations that she got ahead in her career as a result of it. So sure, the president has used it against her, I think as he should, because she's a fraud; and she clearly used it to get ahead in her career.  But it wasn't just him. utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Jesse, what do you think about the argument coming from the left that this is about white grievance and white identity politics, and that Trump is playing into that in that way?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I don't even understand that. I don't understand the question or the sound bite. What does this have to do with white identity politics? utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: They were most upset, 82 percent, that P.C. culture has run amok.  So I guess Native Americans are OK with the Washington Redskins logo now, and they're upset at Elizabeth Warren, the white liberal trying to, you know, assume their -- their ethnicity. utterances.speaker: PAVLICH

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Right, exactly.

utterances.utterance: So Dana, do you understand why the left might say, "Oh, but President Trump, he makes all the Latinos are members of MS-13, out to kill white people."

utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: He didn't say that, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Or "all the blacks are this violence in Chicago. These are violent --"

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes, I understand why they've done it, because I think that they've -- they've either convinced themselves that he believes that or it is -- it's their main line.

utterances.speaker: But they also said that about Republicans before
utterances.utterance: Mitt Romney; even said it about John McCain and George W. Bush. So it is just a line that they've used. utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Good point.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: -- Booker and Harris have had the left media all to themselves to talk about the Kavanaugh hearings. She was figuring out a way to get more attention. I think that, because she is not there in the Judiciary Committee, she's tried this. However I'm going to - - I should write a book about this, but I won't, because we have too many books. She would have run in 2016.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: She would have had the left to herself. She was not the Bernie Sanders guy, but she also was not Hillary. She could have been able to fire up that base. utterances.speaker: PAVLICH
utterances.utterance: Thanks a lot, Hillary. All your fault.

utterances.utterance: Greg, you and I often go back and forth over identity politics.  So I was very curious, because I know you're strong in terms of, you know, deriding the Antifa folks. And I'm thinking to myself, "What would Greg say about that kind of racial -- issue?"

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I'm against -- I'm against all violence, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, good.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And I guess I understood that certain protesters showed up in -- wearing masks. I'm always skeptical of people who wears masks. The KKK wore hoods. And anybody in Antifa who wear masks. I don't think these other fellas were wearing masks, and they showed up at an event. There was vandalism. That's all I know about it, but let's stick to this story, identity politics. You said it's the argument of the left that it's white -- white-based. You have nothing to say about Saudi Arabia. You have nothing to say about Iran. You have nothing to say about black-on-black crime. You have nothing to say about anything, because you're too obsessed with your skin color and who is more oppressed. That's the real crime.  And the candidate that wins for the Democrats is the one who rejects that.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I see. And so what I was talking about, I thought, was identity politics. That's why I raised it with you --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And I answered.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But you see, on the Republican side, I'm amazed that the Republican Club here in New York would host somebody from these Proud Boys.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You'd have to call them, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
